Package: chents
Type: Package
Title: Chemical Entities as R Objects
Version: 0.4.2
Date: 2026-07-03
Authors@R: c(person("Johannes", "Ranke", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
                    email = "johannes.ranke@jrwb.de"))
Description: 
    When working with data on chemical substances, we often need a reliable
    link between the data and the chemical identity of the substances. The R
    package 'chents' provides a way to define an R object corresponding to a
    chemically defined substances, i.e. a chemical entity and to collect
    related information. If Python and 'RDKit' (> 2015.03) are installed and
    configured for use with 'reticulate', some basic chemoinformatics functions
    like the calculation of molecular weight and plotting of chemical
    structures in R graphics are available.
